data.text:
Career Bests

Career Honors

CSCAA First Team All-American

100 Breast (2020, 2021, 2022, 2023, 2024)

200 Medley Relay (2020, 2021, 2022, 2023, 2024)

400 Medley Relay (2022)

Second Team All-Big Ten (2020)

CSCAA First Team Scholar All-American (2020, 2024)

OSU Scholar-Athlete (2020, 2021, 2022, 2023, 2024)

Academic All-Big Ten (2021, 2022, 2023, 2024)

First Team All-Big Ten (2021, 2022, 2023, 2024)

2023-24 (Fifth Year)

Was on the 200 medley relay team that won silver at the NCAA Championships with a time of 1:33.09

Placed sixth in the 100 breast at NCAAs with a time of 57.40 to earn First Team All-American honors

Earned Honorable Mention All-American honors in the 400 medley relay team with a 13th-place finish (3:29.62)

Won the Big Ten title in the 100 breast for the fourth consecutive year with a time of 57.54

Was on the Big Ten champion 200 medley relay (1:33.47) and 400 medley relay (3:28.87) teams

Qualified for the U.S. Olympic Trials in the 100 breast and placed 13th in the semifinals with a time of 1:08.56

2022-23 (Senior)

Earned her third straight Big Ten title in the 100 breast with a time of 58.19

Was on the Big Ten Champion 200 medley relay and 400 medley relay teams

Finished sixth in the 100 breast at the NCAA Championships with a time of 58.08 to earn First Team All-America honors

At the Indy Spring Cup over the summer, turned in an Olympic Trials qualifying time of 1:08.67 in the 100 breast

2021-22 (Junior)

At the NCAA Championships, was part of the third-place 200 medley relay team and the 8th place 400 medley relay team, as well as finishing sixth in the 100 breast

Earned Big Ten titles in the 100 breast, 200 medley relay and 400 medley relay

Placed third in the 200 breast at the Big Ten Championships

2020-21 (Sophomore)

Member of the 200 Medley Relay team that took first vs. Indiana and Purdue on Feb. 6, 2021

Member of the 200 Medley Relay team that won a Big Ten title and set a pool record (1:34.46) at the 2021 Big Ten Championships

Also won a conference title in the 100 Breast and 400 Medley Relay

Swam a personal-best 2:10.98 in the 200 Breast at the conference championship

Earned All-America honors in the 100 Breast and 200 and 400 Medley Relays at the 2021 NCAA Championships to help the Buckeyes to a program-high seventh place finish

2019-20 (Freshman)

Competed in nine different meets in her first season

Won the 100 Breast vs. Kentucky in 1:02.01

Had a great showing at her first Big Ten Championship, scoring points in three events

Started by helping the 200 Medley Relay team to a runner-up finish in a school-record 1:35.17

Swam a personal best and set a new school record with a 58.76 in the prelims of the 100 Breast and then went on to finish eighth in the finals in 1:00.26

Finished the meet with another personal best in the 200 Breast, winning the C final in 2:12.01

Prior to Ohio State

Swam and ran track at Brecksville-Broadview Heights High School

Competed in the breaststroke and freestyle; four year letterwinner

Swam for the Cleveland Sports Institute for four years

Personal

Daughter of Christopher Bach and Sharon Horgan

Has ten siblings, Brenden, Stuart, Emma, Colin, Sara, Garrett, Payton, Rori, Christopher and Brayden

Greatest sports thrill: Attending a Cleveland Browns game when they won
